{"key":"post-12419741","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12419741</id>\n<content>The plastic bag works because it fools the mycelium into not knowing where the edges of the substrate actually are.&amp;nbsp; In nature, cubes tend to fruit at the edges of the substrate, rather than out the very top.&amp;nbsp; Exceptions occur of course, but side fruiting is the natural tendency.&amp;nbsp; The precise conditions we try to provide are intended to trick the mycelium into fruiting over the entire surface.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12419816</next>\n<prev>12419726</prev>\n<first>12419634</first>\n<last>12426871</last>\n<when>1271695628</when>\n<utime>04/19/10 07:47 PM</utime>\n</post>"}